descriptor.name: Toor Daal
descriptor.short_desc: Tur Dal, also known as pigeon pea, is a significant pulse crop in agriculture. It is cultivated for its edible seeds, which are rich in protein and essential nutrients. The Tur Dal plant is a leguminous shrub with compound leaves and yellow flowers. The pods contain the seeds, and these pods mature within 150 to 240 days after sowing.  Tur Dal is well-suited for a variety of climates and soil types, contributing to its widespread cultivation. It is a valuable rotational crop, as it helps in fixing atmospheric nitrogen, enhancing soil fertility. The crop is known for its resilience to drought conditions, making it an important choice in arid and semi-arid regions

descriptor.name: Sprouted Wood Cold Pressed Almond Oil
descriptor.short_desc: Our premium quality Almonds/ Badam produced in India is extracted using a fusion of traditional Wood Cold Pressed Method with modern technology for extraction. We handpicked our Almonds directly from the farms of Kashmir. They are cleaned rigorously and then sun dried non-roasted nuts for the best flavor and aroma.     Our Wood Cold Pressed Almond Oil is pure, Organic, Chemical-free, preservative free and Gluten free. We process the Almonds/ Badam in a wooden Kohlu/pestle or Kachi Ghani that presses the nuts and crushes them for extracting the oil at room temperature. All this is done at a low temperature to keep the temperature of the entire process below 40 degrees. The wood pestle absorbs any increase in temperature and does not generate heat through friction. This technique helps us keep the nutrition maintained in the oil. Once the Oil is extracted, the oil settles for 2-3 days following which, we sieve filter the Almond oil.     Benefits:  Sprouted Wood Cold Pressed Almond Oil is pure and organic hence it will be used less in quantity for cooking as compared with refined oils. Other benefits are:     Contain good amount of Polyunsaturated fats which are good for your health Nuts are pressed and crushed at the same time so the Oil is not refined or polished with chemicals Help in lowering blood sugar levels and improves digestion A good source of antioxidants which protect the body from disease promotes healthy heart Traditional method of extraction keeping all nutrients intact Completely Natural with zero chemicals, aroma or flavor Good source of Vitamin E and antioxidants Good for Skincare and hair care and massage(s)    Our Wood Cold Pressed Almond Oil can be used for dressing, sauteing, seasoning, skincare, haircare, and massage(s).  STORAGE INSTRUCTIONS: Our Wood Cold Pressed Almond Oil is best stored in a cool and dry place with the lid tightly closed.  PACKAGE CONTENT: 1 Wood Cold Pressed Almond Oil; Quantity: 100 ML; Diet Type: Vegetarian; Shelf Life: 365 Days. Our Wood Cold Pressed Almond Oil is 100% made in India.

descriptor.name: Cosmos Organic Sona Masoori Rice
descriptor.short_desc: WHY COSMOS SONA MASOORI RICE  Cosmos Organic Sona Masoori rice is a type of medium-grain, lightweight, aromatic rice that is popular across India. It is called 'Swarna Massori Rice' typically grown using organic farming practices certified by Organic India, which means that no synthetic fertilizers, pesticides, or other chemicals are used during its cultivation. Perfectly aged, rich in energy, nutritious, fluffy, popularly known for its fragrant aroma and soft texture. High in Energy, Protein, and low in Fat, Sugar, and Sodium contents.  Sona Masoori rice, in general, is known for its delicate texture, subtle aroma, and flavor. It is often used in dishes such as biryani, pulao, kheer, sweet pongal, and other varieties of dishes. Organic Sona Masoori rice is considered to be a healthier option compared to conventionally grown rice as it is free from harmful chemicals.  If you are looking to buy, Cosmos Organic Sona Masuri is the ideal choice. Certified by Organic India, Jaivik Bharat, APEDA, and FSSAI-approved laboratory for Nutritional Contents to ensure that it is nutritious, truly organic, and has been grown without any synthetic chemicals.  HEALTH BENEFITS  Pesticides and fertilizer free? Helps improve the immune system Rich in natural proteins, vitamins Aids digestion Aids heart health Helps control calories Good for weight loss diet Fresh and natural COOKING DIRECTIONS   Cooking Ratio: [same for all methods of cooking]  1 cup of Cosmos Sona Masoori white rice  2 cups of water Instructions for cooking in a Pot:   In a medium-sized pot, bring the water to a boil. Add the rice to the pot and stir well.  Reduce the heat to low, cover the pot with a tight-fitting lid, and simmer for 15-20 minutes, or until the rice is fully cooked and the water has been absorbed. Remove the pot from the heat and let it sit for 5-10 minutes with the lid still on. Fluff the rice with a spoon and serve. NOTE: The cooking time may vary slightly depending on the age of the rice and the heat intensity of your stove. You can also adjust the amount of water depending on the desired texture of the cooked rice.  We believe that by choosing Cosmos organic sona masoori white rice, you are not only making a healthy choice for yourself but also supporting sustainable agriculture and protecting the environment.

They are showered with just the right amount of rain and sun-kissed to perfection which allows the grains to be heavy on the palm and amber in colour. These expertly sourced grains undergo mechanised packaging that ensures zero human contact and 100% safety. You and your family can lead a fit and healthier lifestyle as you enjoy soft, fluffy and delicious rotis from this naturally protein-rich whole wheat atta.

descriptor.name: Tata Sampann Moong Dal/Hesaru Bele, 1 kg Pouch
descriptor.short_desc: For most Indians, comfort food is always linked to easy-to-cook homemade meals, and what can be more convenient and quick than preparing a hearty dal meal? Essential in every household, Tata Sampann dals are unpolished and do not undergo any artificial polishing with water, oil or leather, thereby retaining their goodness and wholesome character. The 5-step process ensures that Tata Sampann grains are uniform and of premium quality, giving you an all-natural, authentic taste. A staple in the Indian diet, Moong Dal provides nutrients such as Protein & Fibre. Made of select grains and recommended by Chef Sanjeev Kapoor and Chef Ranveer Brar, Tata Sampann Unpolished Moong Dal makes for a delicious meal choice. So, whenever you are in the mood to cook something easy and delicious, dive into the scrumptious taste of Tata Sampann pulses, and enjoy a lovely meal!
